description: Monstress and Ultra Boy continue to battle Umbra planet-side while the rest of the Legion remain on the Outpost, trying to save Saturn Girl's life. Brainiac 5 learns that the creature that has manifested on the Outpost is a psychic manifestation linked to Saturn Girl and Umbra, so he finds a way to trap it so it won't hurt anyone. While Monstress and Ultra Boy continue to handle Umbra, four different Legionnaires (Spark, Element Boy, LeViathon and Cosmic Boy) approach the Outpost, having finally found the lost Legions..or so it seems.
name: Singularity

description: The rescuing Legionnaires meet the lost Legionnaires on the Outpost and discuss their situation. All the Legionnaires then immediately rush to assist Ultra Boy and Monstress in returning Umbra from the planet below them. They arrive there and Brainiac 5 and Ultra Boy realize that the city they are in is simply an illusion created to placate Singularity, a super powered defender of a utopian society that was no longer needed. The Legion then returns back to the Outpost and heal both Umbra and Saturn Girl but immediately find out that the rescuing Legionnaires were manifestations of Sensor Girl's power subconsciousness, as well as Apparition. The team then feel extremely dejected as Saturn Girl gains consciousness.
name: Lost & Found

description: Saturn Girl relinquishes her leadership to Live Wire, since the team feels wary around her after the incident of last issue. The Legionnaires cope with the possibility of never returning home. Saturn Girl speaks to Ultra Boy and they kiss, lost in their desperation. They soon find a fleet of spaceships racing away and try to follow them, knowing they are escaping from something. Before they can leave, they are approached by a giant fleet of the Progeny.
name: Lost & Alone

description: Wildfire rushed headfirst into the large space fleet of the Progeny, attacking anything within reach. Other Legionnaires assist him in space, attacking the barrage. Before too long, they are held captive by the Progeny. They are told that they will be taken to the Progenitor, the leader of the Progeny. The Legion is surprised to find Element Lad, their fellow Legion of Super-Heroes member, is actually the Progenitor.
name: Rosette

description:
Overview

The astonshing maxi-series nears its stunning conclusion. Defeated by the overwhelming numbers that make up the Progeny forces, the Lost Legionnaires are taken to the Progeny homeworld, where they come face to face with the Progenitor, who reveals how the alien race came to be. The team also discovers Element Lad's fate, but unless they can put their own differences aside, they're in no position to do anything about it.

Spoilers

Element Lad explains to the Legion of Super-Heroes how he became the Progenitor. Back during the incident that caused the Legionnaires to become lost, Element Lad was some shunted to some place outside of the galaxy, where he suffered through time for centuries. He gained a grasp of his powers beyond anything before and began to think of himself as a god, creating the Progeny to do his whim. The Legion try to find a way to stop the Progeny from reaching their area of the galaxy while the Progenitor kills Monstress. The fight is on.
name: One Billion Years Of Solitude

description: The Legion battles the Progenitor, who is also Element Lad, to prevent him from advancing his agenda with his Progeny. The Progenitor reveals that he intends to send the Omniphagos to the rest of the galaxy to destroy everything he believes he created. Saturn Girl is able to use her telepathy to stop the Progenitor for some time while the rest of the Legion tries to stop the technology that allows the Progeny and Omniphagos from transporting to the other side of the galaxy. The team realizes they can make it back home, but someone must destroy the transport after they leave. Live Wire decides to stay behind without telling anyone, sacrificing himself so his team can make it home.
name: First & Last

description: For the first time ever, the classic tale of Batman and Superman's first encounter with Wonder Woman can be told! A billionaire eco-terrorist has unearthed what could be the greatest weapon the world has ever seen: the juggernaut Superman-clone known as Bizarro! The terrorist is joined in his mad quest by a young Amazon warrior with her own malicious agenda. Can three inexperienced heroes bring down this trifecta of evil?

Matt Wagner's (Grendel, Mage) tale of Superman and Batman's first encounter with Wonder Woman continues! Superman pursues a nuclear threat as the Purge comes to Gotham, and the villain's plot to bring about global chaos creeps closer to fruition! Wonder Woman finds herself alone against the twisted fury of Bizarro! And can Batman find a rogue missile in time to avert catastrophe in the city he has sworn to protect?

Matt Wagner's tale featuring DC Comics' greatest super-heroes reaches its breakneck climax! While attempting to save the world from total destruction, an uneasy bond is formed by three new allies. Can they rally to defeat the mysterious eco-terrorist who commands the power to bring the world to its knees?

All’s not well in the Marvel Universe in the year 1602 as strange storms are brewing and strange new powers are emerging! Comics-writing legend and New York Times best-selling author Neil Gaiman (Sandman, American Gods), along with the art team of the best-selling ORIGIN, Andy Kubert and Richard Isanove, brings to life a rich new vision of the Marvel Universe. Spider-Man, the X-Men, Nick Fury, Dr. Strange, Daredevil, Dr. Doom, Black Widow, Captain America and more appear in the waning days of the reign of Queen Elizabeth. As the world begins to change and enter into a new age, Gaiman weaves a thrilling mystery. How and why are these Marvel stars appearing nearly 400 years before they’re supposed to?
name: In Which We Are Introduced To Certain Of Our Players...

description:
What would the Marvel Universe be like 400 years before it's time?

Things have gone a muck in the universe, with well known heroes (Daredevil, Nick Fury, Spider-Man, Dr. Doom) all appearing far before their time. In part two of the epic 1602 adventure things begin to change. Sir Nicholos Fury rides to meet a strange old friend and his odd cohorts. A dark secret is found out about the young miss Virginia Dare. Matthew Murdoch and the mysterious Natasha travell to apprehend a dangerous weapon. Count Otto von Doom is revealed.
name: In Which Things Begin To Change...

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: Matthew Murdoch continues to make his way across Europe to get the mysterious Templar treasure that Dr. Strange thinks will give him the key to the mysterious weather changes. But can he get to it before Otto Von Doom? And what does the first American-born child, Virginia Dare, have to do with it all?
name: In Which There Is Much To Be Learned And The Queen Is Given A Gift.

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: With the Queen gone England has been taken over by James the IV. Sir Nicholos Fury is now, more than ever, sure where his loyalties lie. Natasha betrays poor Matthew Murdoch, Otto von Doom reveals his brilliant mind and more and Peter is captured by Carlos Javier's pupils. Also, the origins of Virginia Dare reveal amazing things and the secret weapon sought after by Stephen Strange is found...but it does not appear as powerful as previously foretold.
name: In Which Much Is Explained And Things Do Not Always Work Out For The Best.

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: Sir Nicholos is forced to go against his old friend, Carlos Javier and his Witchbreed. Can he get them to give themselves up without any lose of life for either side? Peter is discovered among the pupils of Javier and the Inquisitor plots with king James. Matthew Murdoch and old man Donal are captured, we are told the origins of the Four of the Fantastik, Javier, Strange and Fury meet for an important discussion and Stephen Strange gets an explanation.
name: In Which A Treacherous Course Is Plotted

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: Doctor Strange goes to the moon, while our heroes take on Doom and his Vulture squadron!
name: Alarums And Excursions

description: Secrets are revealed and coffins are closed as two of our 17th-century Marvel heroes lose their lives in the penultimate chapter to this major, best-selling limited series event!
name: In Which Many Patterns May Be Discerned, By Those With Eyes To See Them...

description: CLIMATIC last issue! Secrets revealed! Mysteries explained! A mighty sacrifice! Worlds live! Worlds die! Heroes make choices! And so do villains...
name: In Which We Discover The Way Of The World...

description: THE SCOOP: The X-Men's two wild cards unite in one unpredictable adventure! ? THE STORY: Bishop has been captured, and it's up to everyone's favorite ragin' Cajun to free him! There's only one problem: Bishop's captors are the X-Men! What dark forces are behind the X-Men's villainy? And can Gambit survive their combined power?
name: I See A Bad Moon Rising

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: Bishop and Gambit are on the run, and there's only one person they can turn to: the Witness! But isn't he a future version of Gambit? The action heats up as our two mutant outlaws delve deeper into the mystery of their shadowy enemy!
name: Enter... The Witness

description:
It's two of your favorite X-Men in one series! The time-tossed warrior and the ragin' Cajun have been exiled from the X-Men?but even in their darkest hour, why would these two heroes harbor one of their deadliest enemies?

Note: There is a flashback to the founding members of X-Force. Including Copycat using Domino's form.
name: That's Stryfe That#s What People Say

description: It's two of your favorite X-Men in one series! The X-Men have faced many surprises over the years, but none as shocking as the one that Bishop and Gambit discover in this issue!
name: My Brother, My Enemy

description: Two of your favorite X-Men in one series! What will Bishop and Gambit do when faced with making the ultimate sacrifice? And what will they do when forced to take down their shocking foe?
name: Are We Ourselves

description: The grand finale! Who has been stalking Bishop and Gambit since they first escaped from the X-Mansion? What grand scheme have these two X-Men unwittingly been a part of? And will either of them survive the final confrontation with their adversary?
name: What Goes 'Round Comes 'Round!

description:
Black and white reprint of the famous "Saga of the Swamp Thing" #21, one of the most important issues in modern comic book history.

The original plan had been to reprint in color, in the same fashion as Essential Vertigo: Sandman. But black and white reprints already existed for a previous publication, thus making it cheaper to produce.
name: The Anatomy Lesson

description: A black-and-white re-presentation of SAGA OF THE SWAMP THING #35, Part 1 of the 2-part "The Nukeface Papers." As an unscrupulous company dumps nuclear waste into his beloved swamp, Swamp Thing wrestles with visions of a future where nature has given way to a toxic wasteland. But, in the present, a demented vagrant wielding a toxic touch threatens to end Swamp Thing's very existence and make those dark visions a reality. No interior ads.
name: The Nukeface Papers - Part 1

description: What happened when Wolverine and The Thing collided before they donned colorful costumes? This new story reveals all!  The Marvel Universe is full of tough guys, but they just don't come any rougher than Ben Grimm and Logan! This action-packed adventure takes place during Grimm's dangerous days as a test pilot for the U.S. Air Force (before he became the ever lovin' blue eyed idol of millions) and Logan's time as a Canadian secret agent (before he became the X-Men's secret weapon). Needless to say, they get thrown together during a top-secret mission?but can barely stop beating the tar out of each other long enough to get the job done! Featuring appearances by Tony Stark, Nick Fury, Carol Danvers and the Black Widow (and that's just in the first issue), this series sheds light on two of the most interesting (and popular) characters in the Marvel U. during a part of their history we have rarely seen. It's an over-the-top, knuckle-bruising, full throttle adventure, brought to you by the creative team of Larry Hama (WOLVERINE) and red-hot new find Kaare Andrews!
name: Mission to Nowhere

volume.name: Before the Fantastic Four: Ben Grimm and Logan

description: Logan (Wolverine), Ben Grimm (The Thing) and Carol Danvers, trapped behind enemy lines! Shot down and captured by an elite Soviet strike force, our heroes must find a way to escape, that doesn't involve killing each other! Why are they seemingly betrayed? And why does the Black Widow seem to know their next moves? Plus: A prize fight in a speeding train, an escape from a Siberian prison camp, dogfights between experimental aircraft, secret scientific installations, packs of ravenous wolves, a nuclear menace, lots o' stuff blowing up, and surprise cameos by other Marvel mainstays!
name: Midnight Train to Moscow

volume.name: Before the Fantastic Four: Ben Grimm and Logan

description: For your eyes only: the fiery finale of this Cold War caper features a speeding Siberian prison train, a ticked-off Carol Danvers, a hi-jacked Russian jet, a determined Black Widow, Northrop Flying Wing bombers, well-armed Spetsnaz commandos... oh yeah, and a couple of bare-knuckle brawlers named Ben Grimm (The Thing) and Logan (Wolverine)!
name: Connecting Flight

volume.name: Before the Fantastic Four: Ben Grimm and Logan

description: 1st Issue of Katy's first solo book.
